ðŸ’šï¸ Some Points: ðŸ’šï¸

.Fast, efficient and highly sclable
.Event driven, non-blocking I/O model
.Popular in the industry
.Same language on the front and back end (JS)


ðŸ’šï¸ NON-BLOCKING I/O: ðŸ’šï¸

.Works on a single thread using non-blocking I/O calls
.Supports tens of thousands concurrent connections
.Optimizes throughtput & scalability in apps with many I/O Operations


ðŸ’šï¸ NODE'S EVENT LOOP: ðŸ’šï¸

.Single threaded
.Support concurrency via events & callbacks
.EventEmitter class is used to bind events and listeners


ðŸ’šï¸ BEST TYPES OF PROJECTS FOR NODE: ðŸ’šï¸

.REST API & Microservices
.Real Time Services (Chat, Live Updates)
.CRUD Apps - Blogs, shopping Carts, Social Networks
.Tools & Utilities

ðŸ›‘ï¸ Anything that is not CPU intensive


ðŸ’šï¸ NPM - NODE PACKAGE MANAGER:

.install 3rd party packages (frameworks, libraries, tools...)
.Packages get stored in the "node_modules" folder
.All dependencies are listed in a "package.json" file
.NPM scripts can be created to to run certain task

 ðŸ‘¨â€ðŸ’»ï¸ npm init => Generates a package.json file
 ðŸ‘¨â€ðŸ’»ï¸ npm install express => installs a package locally
 ðŸ‘¨â€ðŸ’»ï¸ npm install -g nodemon => installs a package globally 
 
